parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause vibration or pulsation when braking, leading to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal pulsation
vibration in the front end or steering wheel when braking
uneven brake rotor wear
premature wear of brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of brake pads can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noise when braking
excessive brake dust
uneven brake pad wear
premature wear of brake rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaking brake calipers can cause brake fluid loss, leading to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
spongy brake pedal
uneven brake pad wear
premature wear of brake rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle does not latch
the seat belt buckle does not release when opening the door
the seat belt tightens around the driver's neck when shutting and opening immediately
the shoulder belt does not retract in the event of an impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the transmission slips or feels like it's in neutral
the engine RPMs surge or fluctuate
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations.
